      "type": "risk",
      "topic": "security",
      "content": "HTTP hooks are fail-open by design. If Remote Farmer server crashes or network drops, non-2xx/timeout = non-blocking error = Claude Code proceeds as if no hook exists. A network partition means all permissions auto-granted. This is architecturally unfixable from the dashboard side — it's Claude Code's design choice.",
